def calculate_different_sums(x1: int, y1: int, x2: int, y2: int) -> int:
    """
    Calculate the number of possible different sums on the path from cell (x1, y1) to cell (x2, y2),
    where you can only move one cell down or right.

    Parameters:
    x1 (int): The x-coordinate of the start cell.
    y1 (int): The y-coordinate of the start cell.
    x2 (int): The x-coordinate of the end cell.
    y2 (int): The y-coordinate of the end cell.

    Returns:
    int: The number of possible different sums on the path.
    """
    return (x2 - x1) * (y2 - y1) - 1
